window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Most PIs chase bad guys. Astrid Knightstorm chases demons.</b></p> <p>You'd think that after battling a demon, Astrid Knightstorm would deserve a break. No such luck for Austin's premier wizard private detective.</p> <p>Her former master and mentor, Orpheus, has gone off grid. And with rising tensions at the Hellmouth—the literal gateway to the nine realms of hell—she's getting worried.</p> <p>What begins as a fact-finding mission to LA embroils Astrid in a battle to save the world from an invasion of monsters that even an army of vampires struggles to contain.</p> <p>And to win the fight, she must team up with her brother, who walked out on her when she was fourteen.</p> <p>With her past cases coming back to haunt her and a fallen angel facing injustice, Astrid must learn to trust herself and the family she thought abandoned her.</p> <p>Some cases are about fixing problems. This one is about fixing herself.</p> <p><b>Infernal Gate is book three in the electrifying Knightstorm Arcane Investigations urban fantasy series. Perfect for fans of Jim Butcher's Dresden Files, Patricia Briggs, and Ilona Andrews, this fast-paced adventure features a snarky wizard detective, supernatural mysteries, and a world where Magick hides in plain sight.</b></p>"; 
